28/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov and Spanish counterpart Jose Bono sealed a bilateral agreement Monday (28 March) on co-operation in the military sector.
Bono also will meet with Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and Parliament Chairman Borislav Velikov.
In other news Monday, the interior ministry announced that the National Service for the Fight Against Organised Crime had smashed a network involved in trafficking women.
The nearly yearlong operation was conducted in co-operation with Austrian authorities.
(BNR - 28/03/05)
